A [[Singapore]]an term describing the tendency of some local Asians who tend to consider Caucasians superior, usually having a bias towards favouring Caucasians over locals. 

This is a derogatory term that traces its origins from the character of Lieutenant B. F. Pinkerton in the [[Puccini]]'s opera [[Madama Butterfly]]. 

See also [[Sarong Party Girl]].

